===================================================================
--- 
+++ 
@@ -0,0 +1,173 @@
+SELECT name, age, salary FROM employees WHERE id = 10 AND salary > 5000.75 AND active = TRUE;
+
+INSERT INTO accounts (username, password, balance) VALUES ('khaled', 'mypassword', 1200.50);
+
+UPDATE accounts SET balance = balance + 250 WHERE username = 'khaled';
+
+SELECT 'hello ''world''' AS greeting;
+
+SELECT 10, 3.1415, 5e2, .75, 2.5E-3;
+
+SELECT a + b * c - d / e, a >= 10, b <= 20, c != 30;
+
+SELECT first_name, last_name, _hiddenValue123;
+
+SELECT * FROM table1;
+
+SELECT 0x1FA, 0b1010 AS bits;
+
+DECLARE @x INT;
+SET @x = 10;
+
+/* outer start
+   /* inner comment */
+   still in outer
+*/
+SELECT 1;
+
+SELECT name -- this is a comment
+FROM users; -- another comment
+
+SELECT 'line1\
+line2' AS multiline;
+
+SELECT 0xABC\
+DEF AS hex_value;
+
+SELECT * FROM (
+    SELECT id, name 
+    FROM users 
+    WHERE age > 18
+) AS adults
+WHERE name LIKE '%john%';
+
+SELECT 'normal string', 'it''s escaped', @@variable, @user_var;
+
+SELECT a+b, c-d, e*f, g/h, i%j, k&l, m|n, o^p, ~q, r<<2, s>>3;
+
+SELECT * WHERE a = b AND c <> d OR e != f AND g < h OR i > j AND k <= l OR m >= n;
+
+select NAME from USERS where AGE > 18 Order By name ASC;
+
+SELECT '', '''''', '\'escaped', .5, 5., 1e10, 1E-10;
+
+SELECT u.name, o.order_id 
+FROM users u 
+INNER JOIN orders o ON u.id = o.user_id
+LEFT JOIN products p ON o.product_id = p.id;
+
+SELECT department, COUNT(*), AVG(salary) 
+FROM employees 
+GROUP BY department 
+HAVING AVG(salary) > 50000;
+
+SELECT id FROM table1
+UNION
+SELECT id FROM table2
+INTERSECT
+SELECT id FROM table3;
+
+CREATE TABLE users (
+    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
+    username VARCHAR(50) UNIQUE NOT NULL,
+    email VARCHAR(100),
+    age INT CHECK (age >= 18),
+    FOREIGN KEY (department_id) REFERENCES departments(id)
+);
+
+SELECT * FROM products 
+WHERE price BETWEEN 100 AND 500 
+AND category IN ('electronics', 'books', 'clothing')
+AND name LIKE '%special%'
+AND stock > 0;
+
+SELECT name, salary, 
+       ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY department ORDER BY salary DESC) as rank
+FROM employees;
+
+UPDATE stats SET 
+    count += 1,
+    total -= 50,
+    multiplier *= 2,
+    divider /= 4;
+
+SELECT 0b1010\
+1100 AS binary_value;
+
+SELECT /* inline comment */ name, 
+       age,
+       /* multi
+          line
+          comment */ salary
+FROM employees;
+
+SELECT 'quote: ''', 'backslash: \\', 'newline: \n', 'tab: \t', 'mixed: ''\\n''';
+
+/* Level 1
+   /* Level 2
+      /* Level 3 */
+      Back to Level 2
+   */
+   Back to Level 1
+*/
+SELECT 'done';
+
+SELECT @@VERSION, @@IDENTITY, @user_defined, @local_var;
+
+SELECT very_long_identifier_name_with_underscores_and_numbers_123_456_789_ABC;
+
+SELECT 0, 00, 0.0, .0, 0., 1e0, 1E0, 1e+0, 1E-0, 999999999.999999999;
+
+CREATE TEMPORARY TABLE temp_data AS
+SELECT * FROM source
+WHERE EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM other WHERE condition = TRUE)
+FETCH FIRST 10 ROWS ONLY;
+
+SELECT 
+    CASE 
+        WHEN age < 18 THEN 'minor'
+        WHEN age BETWEEN 18 AND 65 THEN 'adult'
+        ELSE 'senior'
+    END AS age_group
+FROM users;
+
+DELETE FROM old_data WHERE created < '2020-01-01';
+INSERT INTO archive SELECT * FROM old_data;
+DROP TABLE old_data;
+CREATE VIEW active_users AS SELECT * FROM users WHERE active = TRUE;
+
+SELECT '''start', 'end''', 'mi''ddle', '''''multiple''''';
+
+SELECT (a + b - c * d / e % f) & g | h ^ ~i << j >> k;
+
+CREATE DATABASE test_db;
+
+/* Create main tables */
+CREATE TABLE departments (
+    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
+    name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL
+);
+
+CREATE TABLE employees (
+    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
+    name VARCHAR(100),
+    salary DECIMAL(10,2),
+    dept_id INT,
+    FOREIGN KEY (dept_id) REFERENCES departments(id)
+);
+
+INSERT INTO departments VALUES (1, 'Engineering'), (2, 'Sales');
+INSERT INTO employees VALUES (1, 'Ahmed', 75000.50, 1), (2, 'Sara', 65000.75, 2);
+
+SELECT 
+    e.name,
+    e.salary,
+    d.name as department,
+    CASE 
+        WHEN e.salary > 70000 THEN 'High'
+        ELSE 'Normal'
+    END as salary_level
+FROM employees e
+INNER JOIN departments d ON e.dept_id = d.id
+WHERE e.salary BETWEEN 60000 AND 80000
+ORDER BY e.salary DESC;
\ No newline at end of file
